President Obama has nominated Waverly D. Crenshaw Jr. and Lawrence Joseph Vilardo to serve on the United States District Courts. Crenshaw has been a partner at Waller Lansden Dortch & Davis, LLP, focusing on labor and employment issues. He has also served as an Assistant Attorney General for the State of Tennessee and as a law clerk to Judge John T. Nixon of the United States District Court for the Middle District of Tennessee. Vilardo has been a partner at Connors & Vilardo, LLP, handling civil and criminal matters. He has also worked as an associate at Damon Morey LLP and as a law clerk to Judge Irving L. Goldberg of the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit. Crenshaw received his J.D. from Vanderbilt University Law School, while Vilardo received his J.D. from Harvard Law School.